==English==
===Alternative forms===
*dead-pan
*dead pan
===Etymology===
A [[compound word]] formed from the [[English]] [[adjective]] ''[[dead]]'' and [[United States]] slang word ''[[pan]]'', which is synonymous to ''"[[face]]"''.
===Pronounciation===
*{{IPA|ˈdɛdpæn}}
===Adjective===
'''deadpan'''
#Delibeately [[impassive]] or [[expressionless]] [[facial expression]]. A person having such a facial expression.

===Noun===
'''deadpan''' (also '''deadpan comedy''' or '''deadpan humour''')
# A style of [[comedic]] [[delivery]] in which something humourous is said or done while not exhibiting a change in emotion or facial expression.